Hello my fellow enthusiasts! The time has come for me to part way with one of my all time favorite firearms, my IWI Desert Eagle Mark XIX. Black in color, and chambered in .44 Magnum. She's treated me very well, and has never failed to amaze me. Nothing but good times/memories. Life is good, but just like any other human being, I was thrown a few curve balls which forces me to let her go. I've put a total of approximately 150 rounds through her. There are few blemishes due to handling, but nothing major, no major scratches or imperfections. She's still gorgeous! The marking in picture near the barrel lock pin is just some oil residue from my last outing. Always torn down and clean after each shooting event. Will come with three EMPTY factory steel magazines. I May or may not have a box of leftover ammo lying around that I can include, just to get you going.

I'm asking $1350 FIRM. Yes, that's in US currency. While I'm mainly interested in a FTF CASH only transaction, I may be willing to entertain those with reasonable trades. Buyer must have a current/valid WA State ID or drivers license. While not having a CPL WILL NOT necessarily bar you from owning this firearm, I usually PREFER to only deal with those who have a current/valid CPL in their possession, so don't be offended if I turn you down because of this. I know the value of my firearm and will not be letting her go for next to nothing. Trade value must be at or above me asking price and must be in my favor as I'm mainly interested in cash at the moment. So, no, I will not trade you for your single plastic firearm. The only firearm that I'm really interested in at the moment is the 4" barrel S&W500, specifically the Backpacker, however, I'm willing to entertain those those with MULTIPLE FIREARM trades, HIGHER-END firearms, or well-conditioned running and driving VEHICLES with current tabs and clean titles.

With all that being said, please feel free to throw your offers my way. I believe I'm a pretty nice, relaxed and understanding guy, The worst that I can possibly say is "Kick rocks your lowlife piece of shit!", okay I'm kidding, but seriously, the worst that I can say is "No, thank you. I appreciate the interest/offer, but I'm going to have to pass. Good luck with everything.", let's face it, it's not that bad right, we've all dealt with rejection one time or another. Email is probably the best way to get a hold of me as I get notifications straight to my phone, however, for those looking for a faster response, please fee free to leave a name and number, and your preferred way of communication i.e. text or phone call and I will get back to you as soon as I possibly can.
